<TITLE> EC will have to answer court if no polls in Dec: Sakhawat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Patuakhali, Nov 13 (bdnews24.com)  The Election Commission will have to answer to the court if the general elections is are not held in December, an election commissioner said on Sunday. They had promised to the Supreme Court that the elections would be held by year-end, M Sakhawat Hossain said at a meeting with the representatives of the civil society and aspiring candidates at Galachipa Upazila in the district "The general election on December 18 and Upazila election on December 28 will be held on schedule," he asserted. The commissioner regretted that 50,000 hajj pilgrims would not be able to vote. "Hajj is more dignified than voting and they (pilgrims) will have chances to vote in future if they are alive." Sakhawat warned of stern actions against rigging and violence. "The perpetrators will be severely dealt with." Modern technology will be used to update the voter list every year, he said. "The Election Commission met thrice with each of the political parties to finalise the election code of conduct and any violation will be punished severely," he said. Replying a question about the registration of Jama'at-e-Islami, Sakhawat said, "Cases against some Jamaat leaders were pending with the court and there are decisions that should be taken by the state, not the Eelection Commission." Presided by Galachipa Upazila Nirbahi officer Abul Kashem Muhammad Mohiuddin, the meeting was also attended by additional deputy commissioner (general) Abdul Mannan and Barisal divisional election commissioner Monirul Islam. A question-and-answer session followed the meeting. Upazila Awami League president Harun-ur Rashid, BNP leader and Chiknikandi UP chairman Shiplu Khan, advocate Shamim Mia, advocate Siddiqur Rahman, Md. Omar Faruk, Malay Dutta and Upazila BNP vice president Siddiqur Rahman, among others, attended it . bdnews24.
